layout.p:
Columns: 35;
                                                  ruled lines: 50 51;
                                                  written lines: 50 51; Uniform layout. Ruling by hard point.Visible pricking and stiching of membranes. 35 columns in total, one to six columns per membrane. No tagin on letters. In some fragments ח is arched.Special shapes of letters occur: the inverted נ placed before and after Num. 10:35-36, פ' לפוף is frequent. Columns generally begin with a new verse. Several instances of majuscular and minuscular letters. The "puncta extraordinaria" placed on the words fixed by masorah.
